title: Singleton Strikers FC
text:
Singleton Strikers Football Club is a semi-professional <a href="Association%20Football">football</a> club based in <a href="Singleton%2C%20New%20South%20Wales">Singleton</a> in the <a href="Hunter%20Region">Hunter Region</a>, <a href="New%20South%20Wales">New South Wales</a>. Singleton Strikers currently compete in the <a href="Northern%20NSW%20State%20League%20Division%201">Northern NSW State League Division 1</a> with teams in First Grade, Reserve Grade and U'18s.
The Northern NSW State League Division 1 is the second tier of football in <a href="Northern%20New%20South%20Wales%20Football">NNSW</a> below the <a href="National%20Premier%20Leagues%20Northern%20NSW">National Premier Leagues Northern NSW</a>.
The Singleton Strikers were crowned champions in the 2020 season, defeating New Lambton 2-0 in the grand final at Magic Park, Captained by the leagues Player of The Year Hayden Nichols. COYS
